			<td class="subhead">Jerry &nbsp;Grossman</td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<td><b>Editor-in-Chief, Photo Industry Reporter,&nbsp;<i>Demystifying Digital</i></b></td>
		</tr>
		
		
		<tr>
			<td><br><img src=/shared_files/techspeakers_photos/Grossman_Jerry.jpg align=left valign="top">&nbsp;Jerry Grossman has been in the photo industry for over 20 years. He began in the advertising business, and joined Nikon as director of advertising in 1993. He held successive marketing positions at Nikon, including vice president of Internet development, where he launched Nikon’s original websites, including NikonNet, the first photo sharing site on the web. He was named Vice President of Marketing for all consumer products in 2001. An avid photo enthusiast, Jerry bought Photo Industry Reporter in April 2005, with the goal of creating an indispensable publication for the photo industry. IN October 2005, his company launched <i>Demystifying Digital</i>, a magazine aimed at helping consumers make sense of today’s technology. He has been on the board for the Eddie Adams Workshop, Make the World a Better Place, the President’s Council for the International Center of Photography and is currently on the Executive Board of the PMDA.</td>
		
		
